lancedb-pro/index.ts:107:  autoRecallMaxChars?: number;\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/index.ts:108:  autoRecallPerItemMaxChars?: number;\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/index.ts:109:  /** Hard per-turn injection cap (safety valve). Overrides autoRecallMaxItems if lower. Default: 10. */\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/index.ts:111:  recallMode?: \"full\" | \"summary\" | \"adaptive\" | \"off\";\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/index.ts:723: * Check if a message should be skipped (slash commands, injected recall/system blocks).\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/index.ts:1271:  /\\b(memory-pro|memory_store|memory_recall|memory_forget|memory_update)\\b/i,\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/index.ts:1294:  // Skip injected context from memory recall\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/index.ts:1977:    // Session-based recall history to prevent redundant injections\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/index.ts:1979:    const recallHistory = new Map<string, Map<string, number>>();\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/index.ts:2229:    // Auto-recall: inject relevant memories before agent starts\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/index.ts:2231:    // recallMode: \"full\" (default when autoRecall=true) | \"summary\" (L0 only) | \"adaptive\" (intent-based) | \"off\"\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/index.ts:2232:    const recallMode = config.recallMode || \"full\";\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/index.ts:2233:    if (config.autoRecall === true && recallMode !== \"off\") {\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/index.ts:2250:      const AUTO_RECALL_TIMEOUT_MS = parsePositiveInt(config.autoRecallTimeoutMs) ?? 5_000; // configurable; default raised from 3s to 5s for remote embedding APIs behind proxies\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/index.ts:2262:          shouldSkipRetrieval(gatingText, config.autoRecallMinLength)\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/index.ts:2269:        // Wrap the entire recall pipeline in a timeout so slow embedding/rerank\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/index.ts:2275:        const recallWork = async (): Promise<{ prependContext: string } | undefined> => {\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/index.ts:2281:          // Auto-recall only needs the user's intent, not full attachment text."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":296,"aggregated":"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/feature_request.yml:45:        - Auto-capture / Auto-recall\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/CHANGELOG.md:11:- **Access reinforcement for time decay**: frequently *manually recalled* memories decay more slowly (spaced-repetition style)\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/CHANGELOG.md:16:- Access reinforcement is gated to manual recall (`source: \\\"manual\\\"`) to avoid auto-recall strengthening noise.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/CHANGELOG.md:30:- **Feat**: Access reinforcement — frequently *manually recalled* memories decay more slowly (spaced-repetition style)\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/CHANGELOG.md:77:- UX: include IDs in agent tool outputs (`memory_recall`, `memory_list`) for easier debugging and `memory_forget` follow-ups.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/CHANGELOG.md:108:- Fix: ghost memories stuck in autoRecall after deletion (#15). BM25-only results from stale FTS index are now validated via `store.hasId()` before inclusion in fused results. Removed the BM25-only floor score of 0.5 that allowed deleted entries to survive `hardMinScore` filtering.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/CHANGELOG.md:109:- Fix: HEARTBEAT pattern now matches anywhere in the prompt (not just at start), preventing autoRecall from triggering on prefixed HEARTBEAT messages.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/CHANGELOG.md:110:- Add: `autoRecallMinLength` config option to set a custom minimum prompt length for autoRecall (default: 15 chars English, 6 CJK). Prompts shorter than this threshold are skipped.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/CHANGELOG.md:115:- Change: set `autoRecall` default to `false` to avoid the model echoing injected `<relevant-memories>` blocks.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/CHANGELOG.md:135:- Fix: auto-recall injection now correctly skips cron prompts wrapped as `[cron:...] run ...` (reduces token usage for cron jobs).\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:9:A LanceDB-backed OpenClaw memory plugin that stores preferences, decisions, and project context, then auto-recalls them in future sessions.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:50:> *(next session — agent auto-recalls your preferences)*\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:55:That's the difference an **AI Memory Assistant** makes — it learns your style, recalls past decisions, and delivers personalized responses without you repeating yourself.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:114:          \"autoRecall\": true,\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:128:- `autoRecall` → relevant memories are injected before each reply\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:187:5. Enable autoCapture, autoRecall, smartExtraction\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:237:- **All 9 MCP tools** used correctly: `memory_recall`, `memory_store`, `memory_forget`, `memory_update`, `memory_stats`, `memory_list`, `self_improvement_log`, `self_improvement_extract_skill`, `self_improvement_review` *(full toolset requires `enableManagementTools: true` — the default Quick Start config exposes the 4 core tools)*\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:238:- **Common pitfall avoidance**: workspace plugin enablement, `autoRecall` default-false, jiti cache, env vars, scope isolation, and more\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:302:| `src/tools.ts` | Agent tool definitions: `memory_recall`, `memory_store`, `memory_forget`, `memory_update` + management tools |\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:326:- **Hybrid Fusion** — vector score as base, BM25 hits receive a weighted boost (not standard RRF — tuned for real-world recall quality)\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:340:| **Hybrid Fusion** | Combines semantic and exact-match recall |\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:358:- **Access Reinforcement**: frequently recalled memories decay slower (spaced-repetition style)\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:372:> **Note (v1.1.0-beta.9+):** Auto-recall now uses the `before_prompt_build` hook instead of the deprecated `before_agent_start`. See [Hook Adaptation](#hook-adaptation-openclaw-20263) below for details.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:427:  \"autoRecall\": true,\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:560:| `tier.coreAccessThreshold` | `10` | Min recall count before promoting to `core` |\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:568:Frequently recalled memories decay more slowly (spaced-repetition style).\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:613:**Option A (lowest-risk):** temporarily disable auto-recall:\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:615:{ \"plugins\": { \"entries\": { \"memory-lancedb-pro\": { \"config\": { \"autoRecall\": false } } } } }\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:618:**Option B (preferred):** keep recall, add to agent system prompt:\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:624:<summary><strong>Auto-recall timeout tuning</strong></summary>\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:626:Auto-recall has a configurable timeout (default 5s) to prevent stalling agent startup. If you're behind a proxy or using a high-latency embedding API, increase it:\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:629:{ \"plugins\": { \"entries\": { \"memory-lancedb-pro\": { \"config\": { \"autoRecallTimeoutMs\": 8000 } } } } }\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:632:If auto-recall consistently times out, check your embedding API latency first. The timeout only affects the automatic injection path — manual `memory_recall` tool calls are not affected.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:684:On ANY tool failure, ALWAYS memory_recall with relevant keywords BEFORE retrying.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README.md:736:| Auto-recall | `before_agent_start` | `before_prompt_build` (priority 10) | `before_agent_start` is deprecated; `before_prompt_build` is the recommended hook for prompt mutation |\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README_CN.md:105:          \"autoRecall\": true,\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README_CN.md:119:- `autoRecall` → 相关记忆在每次回复前自动注入\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README_CN.md:178:5. Enable autoCapture, autoRecall, smartExtraction\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README_CN.md:228:- **全部 9 个 MCP 工具** 的正确用法：`memory_recall`、`memory_store`、`memory_forget`、`memory_update`、`memory_stats`、`memory_list`、`self_improvement_log`、`self_improvement_extract_skill`、`self_improvement_review` *（完整工具集需要设置 `enableManagementTools: true`——默认快速配置仅暴露 4 个核心工具）*\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README_CN.md:229:- **常见坑规避**：workspace 插件启用、`autoRecall` 默认 false、jiti 缓存、环境变量、作用域隔离等\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README_CN.md:293:| `src/tools.ts` | 智能体工具定义：`memory_recall`、`memory_store`、`memory_forget`、`memory_update` + 管理工具 |\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README_CN.md:416:  \"autoRecall\": true,\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README_CN.md:604:{ \"plugins\": { \"entries\": { \"memory-lancedb-pro\": { \"config\": { \"autoRecall\": false } } } } }\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README_CN.md:660:任何工具调用失败时，必须先用 memory_recall 搜索相关关键词，再重试。\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README_DE.md:105:          \"autoRecall\": true,\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/README_DE.md:119:- `autoRecall` → relevante Erinnerungen werden vor 